    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Official nickname for a type of tube-shaped smoothbore portable rocket launcher, held atop the shoulder when fired, introduced as antitank weapons during the Second World War.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
